bugprone-suspicious-include.description:
Description

The check detects various cases when an include refers to what appears to be an
implementation file, which often leads to hard-to-track-down ODR violations.

Examples:

#include
"Dinosaur.hpp"
// OK, .hpp files tend not to have definitions.
#include
"Pterodactyl.h"
// OK, .h files tend not to have definitions.
#include
"Velociraptor.cpp"
// Warning, filename is suspicious.
#include_next <stdio.c>
// Warning, filename is suspicious.
